[src:xxe-prevention/xml-security-cheat-sheet] Since there are no restrictions on the maximum size for the `age` element, this one-million-digit string could be sent to the server for this element.
[src:xxe-prevention/xml-security-cheat-sheet] Typically this type of element should be restricted to contain no more than a certain amount of characters and constrained to a certain set of characters (for example, digits from 0 to 9, the + sign and the - sign).
